@page "/docs"

<PageTitle>Documentation — OpenAPI Guard</PageTitle>

<div class="breadcrumb">
    <a href="/">Home</a> <span>/</span> Documentation
</div>

<div class="page-header">
    <div>
        <h1>Documentation</h1>
        <p class="text-muted" style="margin: 4px 0 0;">Everything you need to get started with OpenAPI Guard.</p>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="docs-grid">
    <!-- Getting Started -->
    <div class="docs-section">
        <div class="gh-box">
            <div class="gh-box-header">
                <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="currentColor" style="vertical-align: -2px; margin-right: 6px;"><path d="M7.47 10.78a.75.75 0 0 0 1.06 0l3.75-3.75a.75.75 0 0 0-1.06-1.06L8.5 8.69V1.75a.75.75 0 0 0-1.5 0v6.94L4.28 5.97a.75.75 0 0 0-1.06 1.06l3.75 3.75ZM3.75 13a.75.75 0 0 0 0 1.5h8.5a.75.75 0 0 0 0-1.5h-8.5Z"/></svg>
                Getting Started
            </div>

            <div class="docs-block">
                <h3>1. Create a Project</h3>
                <p>Each project represents one API or microservice you want to monitor. Navigate to the <strong>Projects</strong> page and click <strong>New project</strong>.</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Give your project a name (e.g. "Identity API", "Payment Service")</li>
                    <li>Add an optional description for your team</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="docs-block">
                <h3>2. Upload Your First Spec</h3>
                <p>Go to the project's <strong>Specs</strong> tab and click <strong>Upload spec</strong>. Paste your OpenAPI v3 specification in JSON or YAML format.</p>
                <div class="docs-callout docs-callout-info">
                    <strong>Tip:</strong> Use a descriptive version label like <code>v1.0.0</code>, <code>prod-2026-03-28</code>, or <code>pr-54</code> so you can easily identify versions later.
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="docs-block">
                <h3>3. Upload a Second Spec</h3>
                <p>Upload a new version of your spec. This could be from a pull request, a staging environment, or a newer release.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="docs-block">
                <h3>4. Compare and Detect Changes</h3>
                <p>On the <strong>Specs</strong> tab, use the <strong>Compare</strong> section to select a "From" and "To" version, then click <strong>Compare</strong>. OpenAPI Guard will analyse both specs and generate a detailed diff report showing:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><span class="badge badge-fail">Breaking</span> — Changes that will break existing clients</li>
                    <li><span class="badge badge-warning">Warning</span> — Potentially risky changes to review</li>
                    <li><span class="badge badge-info">Info</span> — Non-breaking additions or improvements</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- What Gets Detected -->
    <div class="docs-section">
        <div class="gh-box">
            <div class="gh-box-header">
                <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="currentColor" style="vertical-align: -2px; margin-right: 6px;"><path d="M8 1.5c-2.363 0-4 1.69-4 3.75 0 .984.424 1.625.984 2.304l.214.253c.223.264.47.556.673.848.284.411.537.896.621 1.49a.75.75 0 0 1-1.484.211c-.04-.282-.163-.547-.37-.847a8.456 8.456 0 0 0-.542-.68c-.084-.1-.173-.205-.268-.32C3.201 7.75 2.5 6.766 2.5 5.25 2.5 2.31 4.863 0 8 0s5.5 2.31 5.5 5.25c0 1.516-.701 2.5-1.328 3.259-.095.115-.184.22-.268.319-.207.245-.383.453-.541.681-.208.3-.33.565-.37.847a.751.751 0 0 1-1.485-.212c.084-.593.337-1.078.621-1.489.203-.292.45-.584.673-.848.075-.088.147-.173.213-.253.561-.679.985-1.32.985-2.304 0-2.06-1.637-3.75-4-3.75ZM5.75 12h4.5a.75.75 0 0 1 0 1.5h-4.5a.75.75 0 0 1 0-1.5ZM6 15.25a.75.75 0 0 1 .75-.75h2.5a.75.75 0 0 1 0 1.5h-2.5a.75.75 0 0 1-.75-.75Z"/></svg>
                What Gets Detected
            </div>

            <div class="docs-block">
                <h3>Breaking Changes</h3>
                <table class="gh-table">
                    <thead>
                        <tr><th>Change</th><th>Severity</th></tr>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody>
                        <tr><td>Endpoint removed</td><td><span class="badge badge-fail">Breaking</span></td></tr>
                        <tr><td>Required parameter added</td><td><span class="badge badge-fail">Breaking</span></td></tr>
                        <tr><td>Parameter type changed</td><td><span class="badge badge-fail">Breaking</span></td></tr>
                        <tr><td>Optional parameter becomes required</td><td><span class="badge badge-fail">Breaking</span></td></tr>
                        <tr><td>Response field removed</td><td><span class="badge badge-fail">Breaking</span></td></tr>
                        <tr><td>Response field type changed</td><td><span class="badge badge-fail">Breaking</span></td></tr>
                        <tr><td>Required field added to request body</td><td><span class="badge badge-fail">Breaking</span></td></tr>
                    </tbody>
                </table>
            </div>

            <div class="docs-block">
                <h3>Informational Changes</h3>
                <table class="gh-table">
                    <thead>
                        <tr><th>Change</th><th>Severity</th></tr>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody>
                        <tr><td>New endpoint added</td><td><span class="badge badge-info">Info</span></td></tr>
                        <tr><td>New optional response field added</td><td><span class="badge badge-info">Info</span></td></tr>
                        <tr><td>New optional request body field</td><td><span class="badge badge-info">Info</span></td></tr>
                    </tbody>
                </table>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Rules & Configuration -->
    <div class="docs-section">
        <div class="gh-box">
            <div class="gh-box-header">
                <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="currentColor" style="vertical-align: -2px; margin-right: 6px;"><path d="M8 0a8.2 8.2 0 0 1 .701.031C9.444.095 9.99.645 10.16 1.29l.288 1.107c.018.066.079.158.212.224.231.114.454.243.668.386.123.082.233.09.299.071l1.1-.303c.652-.18 1.34.03 1.73.552a7.968 7.968 0 0 1 .7 1.209c.228.469.095 1.038-.318 1.403l-.838.718c-.05.042-.1.132-.1.279 0 .085.011.194.036.294.022.09.04.146.04.146l.837.718c.414.365.546.934.318 1.403a7.968 7.968 0 0 1-.7 1.209c-.39.522-1.078.732-1.73.552l-1.1-.303c-.066-.018-.176-.011-.299.071a5.254 5.254 0 0 1-.668.386c-.133.066-.194.158-.212.224l-.288 1.107c-.17.645-.716 1.195-1.459 1.26a8.006 8.006 0 0 1-1.402 0c-.743-.065-1.289-.615-1.459-1.26l-.288-1.107c-.018-.066-.079-.158-.212-.224a5.738 5.738 0 0 1-.668-.386c-.123-.082-.233-.09-.299-.071l-1.1.303c-.652.18-1.34-.03-1.73-.552a7.968 7.968 0 0 1-.7-1.209c-.228-.469-.095-1.038.318-1.403l.838-.718c.05-.042.1-.132.1-.279a2.077 2.077 0 0 0-.036-.294c-.022-.09-.04-.146-.04-.146l-.837-.718c-.414-.365-.546-.934-.318-1.403.192-.396.424-.764.7-1.209.39-.522 1.078-.732 1.73-.552l1.1.303c.066.018.176.011.299-.071.214-.143.437-.272.668-.386.133-.066.194-.158.212-.224l.288-1.107C6.01.645 6.556.095 7.299.03 7.53.01 7.764 0 8 0Zm-.571 1.525c-.036.003-.108.036-.137.146l-.289 1.105c-.147.561-.549.967-.998 1.189-.173.086-.34.183-.5.29-.417.278-.97.423-1.529.27l-1.103-.303c-.109-.03-.175.016-.195.046-.219.31-.41.641-.573.989-.014.031-.022.11.059.19l.839.72c.427.365.66.896.66 1.433s-.233 1.068-.66 1.433l-.84.72c-.08.08-.073.159-.058.19.162.348.354.678.573.989.02.03.085.076.195.046l1.102-.303c.56-.153 1.113-.008 1.53.27.16.107.327.204.5.29.449.222.851.628.998 1.189l.289 1.105c.029.11.101.143.137.146a6.6 6.6 0 0 0 1.142 0c.036-.003.108-.036.137-.146l.289-1.105c.147-.561.549-.967.998-1.189.173-.086.34-.183.5-.29.417-.278.97-.423 1.529-.27l1.103.303c.109.03.175-.016.195-.046.219-.31.41-.641.573-.989.014-.031.022-.11-.059-.19l-.839-.72c-.427-.365-.66-.896-.66-1.433s.233-1.068.66-1.433l.84-.72c.08-.08.073-.159.058-.19a6.048 6.048 0 0 0-.573-.989c-.02-.03-.085-.076-.195-.046l-1.102.303c-.56.153-1.113.008-1.53-.27a4.44 4.44 0 0 0-.5-.29c-.449-.222-.851-.628-.998-1.189l-.289-1.105c-.029-.11-.101-.143-.137-.146a6.6 6.6 0 0 0-1.142 0ZM11 8a3 3 0 1 1-6 0 3 3 0 0 1 6 0ZM9.5 8a1.5 1.5 0 1 0-3.001.001A1.5 1.5 0 0 0 9.5 8Z"/></svg>
                Rules &amp; Configuration
            </div>

            <div class="docs-block">
                <h3>Breaking Change Policy</h3>
                <p>Configure which breaking changes should fail a diff check. Go to your project's <strong>Rules</strong> tab to toggle:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Block removed endpoints</strong> — Fail when an endpoint is deleted</li>
                    <li><strong>Block removed response fields</strong> — Fail when a response field disappears</li>
                    <li><strong>Block type changes</strong> — Fail when a field changes type (e.g. <code>string</code> → <code>integer</code>)</li>
                    <li><strong>Block optional → required</strong> — Fail when an optional field becomes required</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="docs-block">
                <h3>API Standards</h3>
                <p>Enforce governance rules on your OpenAPI specs:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Require auth scheme</strong> — Spec must define a security scheme</li>
                    <li><strong>Require 4xx/5xx responses</strong> — Every endpoint must document error responses</li>
                    <li><strong>Require operationId</strong> — Every operation needs a unique identifier</li>
                    <li><strong>Naming convention</strong> — Enforce camelCase or snake_case across your API</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- GitHub Integration -->
    <div class="docs-section">
        <div class="gh-box">
            <div class="gh-box-header">
                <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="currentColor" style="vertical-align: -2px; margin-right: 6px;"><path d="M8 0c4.42 0 8 3.58 8 8a8.013 8.013 0 0 1-5.45 7.59c-.4.08-.55-.17-.55-.38 0-.27.01-1.13.01-2.2 0-.75-.25-1.23-.54-1.48 1.78-.2 3.65-.88 3.65-3.95 0-.88-.31-1.59-.82-2.15.08-.2.36-1.02-.08-2.12 0 0-.67-.22-2.2.82-.64-.18-1.32-.27-2-.27-.68 0-1.36.09-2 .27-1.53-1.03-2.2-.82-2.2-.82-.44 1.1-.16 1.92-.08 2.12-.51.56-.82 1.28-.82 2.15 0 3.06 1.86 3.75 3.64 3.95-.23.2-.44.55-.51 1.07-.46.21-1.61.55-2.33-.66-.15-.24-.6-.83-1.23-.82-.67.01-.27.38.01.53.34.19.73.9.82 1.13.16.45.68 1.31 2.69.94 0 .67.01 1.3.01 1.49 0 .21-.15.45-.55.38A7.995 7.995 0 0 1 0 8c0-4.42 3.58-8 8-8Z"/></svg>
                GitHub Integration
            </div>

            <div class="docs-block">
                <h3>Link a Repository</h3>
                <p>In your project's <strong>Settings</strong> tab, you can link a GitHub repository. This stores the repo URL, default branch, and the path to your OpenAPI spec file.</p>
                <div class="docs-callout docs-callout-warning">
                    <strong>Note:</strong> In the current MVP, the repository link is stored for reference only. Automatic spec fetching from GitHub will be available in a future release.
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="docs-block">
                <h3>Planned Features</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Auto-fetch specs from GitHub on push/PR</li>
                    <li>GitHub PR status checks (pass/fail on breaking changes)</li>
                    <li>GitHub Actions integration for CI/CD pipelines</li>
                    <li>Webhook notifications on breaking changes</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Supported Formats -->
    <div class="docs-section">
        <div class="gh-box">
            <div class="gh-box-header">
                <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="currentColor" style="vertical-align: -2px; margin-right: 6px;"><path d="M4 0a2 2 0 0 0-2 2v12a2 2 0 0 0 2 2h8a2 2 0 0 0 2-2V4.5L9.5 0H4Zm5.5 1.5 3 3H10a.5.5 0 0 1-.5-.5V1.5ZM4 1h5v3a1.5 1.5 0 0 0 1.5 1.5H13v8.5a.5.5 0 0 1-.5.5h-9a.5.5 0 0 1-.5-.5V2a1 1 0 0 1 1-1Z"/></svg>
                Supported Formats
            </div>

            <div class="docs-block">
                <h3>OpenAPI v3 Only</h3>
                <p>OpenAPI Guard supports <strong>OpenAPI Specification v3.0.x</strong> and <strong>v3.1.x</strong>. Swagger v2 (OpenAPI 2.0) specs are rejected with a clear error message.</p>
                <p>Accepted formats:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>JSON</strong> — Standard JSON format</li>
                    <li><strong>YAML</strong> — YAML format (converted internally)</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="docs-block">
                <h3>Input Methods</h3>
                <p>Currently supported:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Paste</strong> — Copy and paste your spec directly into the upload form</li>
                </ul>
                <p style="color: var(--color-text-muted); font-size: 12px;">File upload and URL fetch coming soon.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- FAQ -->
    <div class="docs-section">
        <div class="gh-box">
            <div class="gh-box-header">
                <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="currentColor" style="vertical-align: -2px; margin-right: 6px;"><path d="M0 8a8 8 0 1 1 16 0A8 8 0 0 1 0 8Zm8-6.5a6.5 6.5 0 1 0 0 13 6.5 6.5 0 0 0 0-13ZM6.92 6.085h.001a.749.749 0 1 1-1.342-.67c.169-.339.516-.644.918-.82.404-.178.907-.26 1.417-.13a1.666 1.666 0 0 1 1.193 1.308c.091.53-.08.968-.405 1.288-.236.233-.577.417-.898.533l-.013.005v.77a.75.75 0 0 1-1.5 0v-1.263a.75.75 0 0 1 .549-.723c.412-.12.762-.282.95-.468.026-.025.076-.094.053-.226a.166.166 0 0 0-.12-.132c-.123-.032-.3-.017-.469.062-.19.089-.346.238-.398.378ZM8 10.5a1 1 0 1 1 0 2 1 1 0 0 1 0-2Z"/></svg>
                FAQ
            </div>

            <div class="docs-block">
                <h3>What counts as a breaking change?</h3>
                <p>Any change that could cause existing API consumers to fail: removing endpoints, removing response fields, changing field types, making optional parameters required, or changing parameter types.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="docs-block">
                <h3>Can I self-host OpenAPI Guard?</h3>
                <p>Yes. OpenAPI Guard is designed to run both as a SaaS product and self-hosted. Clone the repository, configure your PostgreSQL connection string, and run with <code>dotnet run</code> or Docker.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="docs-block">
                <h3>What database is required?</h3>
                <p>PostgreSQL 14 or higher. A Docker Compose file is included for quick local setup.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="docs-block">
                <h3>Is there a size limit on specs?</h3>
                <p>There is no hard limit in the MVP. Very large specs (10,000+ lines) may take a few seconds to parse and compare.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
